       tive nonsense by mapping ASCII into Dvorak keyboard equiv-
       alents  using  the  Dvorak table.  The table is assumed to
       reside in the file /usr/lib/kbd/Dvorak.  The existing out-
       put file is overwritten: kbdpipe -F -t Dvorak -o iapxai.vj
       file1 file2

       The following example loads the Dvorak table from  a  dif-
       ferent file, then converts standard input to standard out-
       put.  The Dvorak table (assumed  to  be  non-resident)  is
       explicitly  loaded  from an absolute path beginning at the
       user's   home   directory:   kbdpipe    -t    Dvorak    -f
       $HOME/tables/Dvorak.tab

