       Because kbdpipe uses to load  tables,  it  cannot  resolve
       link references.  Therefore, if a composite table is used,
       the relevant portions must either be  already  loaded  and
       public,  or  be  contained  in  the  file used (via the -f
       option) on the command line.  In the latter case, the com-
       posite  elements  must  be  loaded  earlier  than the link
       entry.

       Users may use kbd tables in  programs  at  user  level  by
       opening  a  pipe,  pushing  the  module,  and  setting via
       related commands.  Therefore, there is no need to use  the
       kbdpipe  command.   kbdpipe may not be supported in future
       releases.

